nt.\"\n\nThe core disagreement centers on whether pUSD qualifies as a launched token or merely represents infrastructure collateral. The plaintiff emphasizes that pUSD satisfies all four proposition elements: it's fungible as an ERC-20, officially released by Polymarket, publicly communicated through official channels, and deployed before the deadline.\n\nThe defendant counters that pUSD functions as a technical settlement wrapper rather than a genuine token launch, pointing to Polymarket's own distinction between pUSD collateral and any future token generation event.\n\nUnder preponderance, the question becomes whether an official ERC-20 collateral token deployed in production and documented by Polymarket counts as launching an official fungible token. The proposition doesn't require a governance token, airdrop, TGE, or external exchange listing—it only excludes NFTs, promotional offerings, points systems, and collaboration tokens. pUSD meets the stated criteria: it's an official Polymarket ERC-20, publicly documented, and launched before the deadline.\n\nThe defense's distinction between \"collateral infrastructure\" and \"token launch\" reads limitations into the proposition that aren't there. An official ERC-20 token deployed by Polymarket, documented on official channels, and actively used in production satisfies what the proposition actually requires.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"text":"","type":"text"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782822962-iqYw289OeY5lnb8mBo6j","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782822962624,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"message_update"}
