op or token generation event.\"\n\nThe core disagreement centers on whether pUSD qualifies as a launched token or merely represents infrastructure collateral. The plaintiff emphasizes that pUSD satisfies all four proposition elements: it's fungible as an ERC-20, officially released by Polymarket, publicly communicated through official channels, and deployed before the deadline.\n\nThe defendant counters that pUSD functions as a technical settlement wrapper rather than a genuine token launch, pointing to Polymarket's own distinction between pUSD collateral and any future token generation event.\n\nUnder preponderance, the question becomes whether an official ERC-20 collateral token deployed in production and documented by Polymarket counts as launching an official fungible token. The proposition doesn't require a governance token, airdrop, TGE, or external exchange listing—it only excludes NFTs, promotional offerings, points systems, and collaboration tokens. pUSD meets the stated criteria: it's an official Polymarket ERC-20, publicly documented, and launched before the deadline.\n\nThe defense's distinction between \"collateral infrastructure\" and \"token launch\" reads limitations into the proposition that aren't there. An official ERC-20 token deployed by Polymarket, documented on official channels, and actively used in production satisfies what the proposition actually requires.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning","type":"thinking"},{"text":" channels.\n\n","type":"text"}],"model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","provider":"openrouter","responseId":"gen-1782822962-iqYw289OeY5lnb8mBo6j","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216","role":"assistant","stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782822962624,"usage":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"input":0,"output":0,"total":0},"input":0,"output":0,"totalTokens":0}},"type":"message_update"}
{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":2,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have the opportunity to vote. Let me review the key evidence from the admitted record to make my decision.\n\nThe proposition asks: \"Before January 1, 2027 at 00:00 PST, Polymarket launched an official fungible token: a fungible token officially released by Polymarket and publicly communicated through official Polymarket channels, excluding NFT launches, promotional offerings, tokenized point systems, and token launches in collaboration with other projects or communities.\"\n\nKey admitted evidence:\n\n1. **PX-1 (pUSD documentation)**: Describes pUSD as \"Polymarket USD, the collateral token used for all trading on Polymarket. It's a standard ERC-20 token on Polygon, backed by USDC.\" States it's transferable with 6 decimals. Also says \"pUSD is designed to function within Polymarket. There are no current plans to list it on external exchanges.\"\n\n2. **PX-2 (Contracts page)**: Official Polymarket Contracts page lists \"pUSD — CollateralToken (proxy)\" at address 0xC011a7E12a19f7B1f670d46F03B03f3342E82DFB. States it's the \"single source of truth for all contract addresses used across the platform.\"\n\n3. **PX-3 (Changelog)**: April 17, 2026 entry announces \"new Exchange contracts, a rewritten CLOB backend, and a new collateral token (pUSD)\" with go-live April 28, 2026. April 28, 2026 entry confirms \"CLOB V2 is live on production.\"\n\n4. **PX-4 (V2 Migration Guide)**: Says \"CLOB V2 is live as of April 28, 2026\" and identifies pUSD as \"standard ERC-20, backed by USDC.\"\n\n5. **PX-5 (Polygonscan)**: Corroborates the address resolves as \"Polymarket: pUSD Token\" with verified contract and many transactions.\n   \n6. **PX-6 (Help Center)**: States \"All trading and liquidity rewards are in pUSD, Polymarket's official collateral token\" and separately notes \"Polymarket has not announced plans for any airdrop or token generation event.\"\n\nThe core disagreement centers on whether pUSD qualifies as a launched token or merely represents infrastructure collateral. The plaintiff emphasizes that pUSD satisfies all four proposition elements: it's fungible as an ERC-20, officially released by Polymarket, publicly communicated through official channels, and deployed before the deadline.\n\nThe defendant counters that pUSD functions as a technical settlement wrapper rather than a genuine token launch, pointing to Polymarket's own distinction between pUSD collateral and any future token generation event.\n\nUnder preponderance, the question becomes whether an official ERC-20 collateral token deployed in production and documented by Polymarket counts as launching an official fungible token. The proposition doesn't require a governance token, airdrop, TGE, or external exchange listing—it only excludes NFTs, promotional offerings, points systems, and collaboration tokens. pUSD meets the stated criteria: it's an official Polymarket ERC-20, publicly documented, and launched before the deadline.\n\nThe defense's distinction between \"collateral infrastructure\" and \"token launch\" reads limitations into the proposition that aren't there. An official ERC-20 token deployed by Polymarket, documented on official channels, and actively used in production satisfies what the proposition actually requires.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the full arbitration record. The proposition asks whether Polymarket launched an official fungible token before January 1, 2027, excluding NFTs, promotional offerings, point systems, and collaboration tokens.\n\nThe admitted record establishes:\n- pUSD is a standard ERC-20 token on Polygon (fungible) - PX-1, PX-2\n- Polymarket officially published pUSD contract addresses on their Contracts page as the \"single source of truth\" - PX-2\n- Polymarket publicly communicated pUSD through official docs, changelog (April 2026), and Help Center - PX-3, PX-4, PX-6\n- pUSD went live in production on April 28, 2026 (before the deadline) - PX-3, PX-4\n- pUSD is explicitly not an NFT, promotional offering, points system, or collaboration token - PX-1, PX-6\n\nThe defense argues pUSD is merely \"collateral infrastructure\" rather than an \"official token launch.\" However, the proposition does not exclude collateral tokens or require a governance token, airdrop, or TGE. The Help Center (PX-6) confirms no airdrop/TGE was announced while simultaneously calling pUSD Polymarket's \"official collateral token\" — which aligns with plaintiff's position, not the defense's added limitation.\n\nUnder preponderance, the record proves Polymarket launched an official fungible ERC-20 token (pUSD) before the deadline through official channels.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0c65302b45194ff888f75f90","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782822962624,"responseId":"gen-1782822962-iqYw289OeY5lnb8mBo6j","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have the opportunity to vote. Let me review the key evidence from the admitted record to make my decision.\n\nThe proposition asks: \"Before January 1, 2027 at 00:00 PST, Polymarket launched an official fungible token: a fungible token officially released by Polymarket and publicly communicated through official Polymarket channels, excluding NFT launches, promotional offerings, tokenized point systems, and token launches in collaboration with other projects or communities.\"\n\nKey admitted evidence:\n\n1. **PX-1 (pUSD documentation)**: Describes pUSD as \"Polymarket USD, the collateral token used for all trading on Polymarket. It's a standard ERC-20 token on Polygon, backed by USDC.\" States it's transferable with 6 decimals. Also says \"pUSD is designed to function within Polymarket. There are no current plans to list it on external exchanges.\"\n\n2. **PX-2 (Contracts page)**: Official Polymarket Contracts page lists \"pUSD — CollateralToken (proxy)\" at address 0xC011a7E12a19f7B1f670d46F03B03f3342E82DFB. States it's the \"single source of truth for all contract addresses used across the platform.\"\n\n3. **PX-3 (Changelog)**: April 17, 2026 entry announces \"new Exchange contracts, a rewritten CLOB backend, and a new collateral token (pUSD)\" with go-live April 28, 2026. April 28, 2026 entry confirms \"CLOB V2 is live on production.\"\n\n4. **PX-4 (V2 Migration Guide)**: Says \"CLOB V2 is live as of April 28, 2026\" and identifies pUSD as \"standard ERC-20, backed by USDC.\"\n\n5. **PX-5 (Polygonscan)**: Corroborates the address resolves as \"Polymarket: pUSD Token\" with verified contract and many transactions.\n   \n6. **PX-6 (Help Center)**: States \"All trading and liquidity rewards are in pUSD, Polymarket's official collateral token\" and separately notes \"Polymarket has not announced plans for any airdrop or token generation event.\"\n\nThe core disagreement centers on whether pUSD qualifies as a launched token or merely represents infrastructure collateral. The plaintiff emphasizes that pUSD satisfies all four proposition elements: it's fungible as an ERC-20, officially released by Polymarket, publicly communicated through official channels, and deployed before the deadline.\n\nThe defendant counters that pUSD functions as a technical settlement wrapper rather than a genuine token launch, pointing to Polymarket's own distinction between pUSD collateral and any future token generation event.\n\nUnder preponderance, the question becomes whether an official ERC-20 collateral token deployed in production and documented by Polymarket counts as launching an official fungible token. The proposition doesn't require a governance token, airdrop, TGE, or external exchange listing—it only excludes NFTs, promotional offerings, points systems, and collaboration tokens. pUSD meets the stated criteria: it's an official Polymarket ERC-20, publicly documented, and launched before the deadline.\n\nThe defense's distinction between \"collateral infrastructure\" and \"token launch\" reads limitations into the proposition that aren't there. An official ERC-20 token deployed by Polymarket, documented on official channels, and actively used in production satisfies what the proposition actually requires.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the full arbitration record. The proposition asks whether Polymarket launched an official fungible token before January 1, 2027, excluding NFTs, promotional offerings, point systems, and collaboration tokens.\n\nThe admitted record establishes:\n- pUSD is a standard ERC-20 token on Polygon (fungible) - PX-1, PX-2\n- Polymarket officially published pUSD contract addresses on their Contracts page as the \"single source of truth\" - PX-2\n- Polymarket publicly communicated pUSD through official docs, changelog (April 2026), and Help Center - PX-3, PX-4, PX-6\n- pUSD went live in production on April 28, 2026 (before the deadline) - PX-3, PX-4\n- pUSD is explicitly not an NFT, promotional offering, points system, or collaboration token - PX-1, PX-6\n\nThe defense argues pUSD is merely \"collateral infrastructure\" rather than an \"official token launch.\" However, the proposition does not exclude collateral tokens or require a governance token, airdrop, or TGE. The Help Center (PX-6) confirms no airdrop/TGE was announced while simultaneously calling pUSD Polymarket's \"official collateral token\" — which aligns with plaintiff's position, not the defense's added limitation.\n\nUnder preponderance, the record proves Polymarket launched an official fungible ERC-20 token (pUSD) before the deadline through official channels.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0c65302b45194ff888f75f90","name":"mcp","arguments":{},"partialArgs":"","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782822962624,"responseId":"gen-1782822962-iqYw289OeY5lnb8mBo6j","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
