 their Contracts page as the \"single source of truth\" - PX-2\n- Polymarket publicly communicated pUSD through official docs, changelog (April 2026), and Help Center - PX-3, PX-4, PX-6\n- pUSD went live in production on April 28, 2026 (before the deadline) - PX-3, PX-4\n- pUSD is explicitly not an NFT, promotional offering, points system, or collaboration token - PX-1, PX-6\n\nThe defense argues pUSD is merely \"collateral infrastructure\" rather than an \"official token launch.\" However, the proposition does not exclude collateral tokens or require a governance token, airdrop, or TGE. The Help Center (PX-6) confirms no airdrop/TGE was announced while simultaneously calling pUSD Polymarket's \"official collateral token\" — which aligns with plaintiff's position, not the defense's added limitation.\n\nUnder preponderance, the record proves Polymarket launched an official fungible ERC-20 token (pUSD) before the deadline through official channels.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0c65302b45194ff888f75f90","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted record proves by preponderance that Polymarket launched pUSD, an official fungible ERC-20 token, before January 1, 2027. Official Polymarket documentation (PX-1 through PX-4, PX-6) publicly described, published contract addresses for, and deployed pUSD to production on April 28, 2026. The proposition excludes NFTs, promotions"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted record proves by preponderance that Polymarket launched pUSD, an official fungible ERC-20 token, before January 1, 2027. Official Polymarket documentation (PX-1 through PX-4, PX-6) publicly described, published contract addresses for, and deployed pUSD to production on April 28, 2026. The proposition excludes NFTs, promotions","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"o